`uninstall.cmd` is a 23-line batch script bundled with the Dropbox updater. It accepts `--dir <path>` and recursively deletes the directory. Before deleting, it tries to ensure the path is "an updater install path" by checking that the path contains the substring `\Dropbox\DropboxUpdater`:

```batch
@echo %Directory% | FindStr /L \Dropbox\DropboxUpdater > nul
if %ERRORLEVEL% NEQ 0 (
  echo "Invalid argument."
  exit 2
)

for /L %%G IN (1,1,15) do (
  ping -n 2 127.0.0.1 > nul
  rmdir %Directory%
